@prefix : <https://www.w3id.org/climoo/climoo-sdc2#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@base <https://www.w3id.org/climoo/climoo-sdc2#> .

<https://www.w3id.org/climoo/climoo-sdc2> rdf:type owl:Ontology ;
                                           owl:versionIRI :sdc2-v1.0.0 ;
                                           owl:imports <http://ClimOO/climoo/climoo-sdc2/imports/cco-imports#2026-04-09> ,
                                                       <http://ClimOO/climoo/climoo-sdc2/imports/sdc-ontology-imports/sdc-ontology-gdc-imports#2026-04-08> ,
                                                       <https://www.w3id.org/sco/sco-b#v1.1.0/sco-b> ;
                                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> "Giorgio A. Ubbiali" ,
                                                                                  "Ludger Jansen" ;
                                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Giorgio A. Ubbiali" ;
                                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> """ClimOO Ontology is a reference ontology, modeling plastics, (micro-)plastic pollution, climate change, and their interrelation, with a primary focus on agricultural systems. The ClimOO Ontology is structured in a suite of nested ontological modules.The SDC2 module forks the Sustainable Development and Climate (SDC) Ontology, updating the proposed models. The SDC2 module centers on climate and climate change, especially with regard to environmental features and related interconnections. Emphasis is also dedicated to relevant policies.

SDC ontology: https://github.com/hbabaie1/Sustainable-Development-and-Climate-SDC-ontology"""@en ;
                                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" ;
                                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "ClimOO Ontology - ClimOO-SDC2 module"@en ;
                                           rdfs:comment """The SDC Ontology provides a relevant model of climate and climate change, primarily with a focus on Sustainable Development Goals (Davarpanah et al., 2023). Despite its relevance, the SDC Onto model appears undermaintained and presents several shortcomings, including:
• Inconsistent hierarchy root.
• Absence of natural language definitions.
• Reusage of PATO representations that violate the BFO model, such as those concerning process properties, or that are inaccurate, such as those concerning increased and decreased dependent continuants.
• Misleadingness of certain classes.
• Inadequate axiomatization of certain classes.
For more details, see here (coming soon).

Thus, we forked SDC Onto to develop a novel version, named ClimOO-SDC2. ClimOO-SDC2 is the module of the ClimOO Ontology dedicated to climate change. ClimOO-SDC2 focuses on environmental features and related interconnections modeled in SDC Onto. ClimOO-SDC2 offers an active reference hub that addresses SDC Onto's shortcomings, while integrating the SDC Onto model into the ClimOO Ontology. ClimOO-SDC2 extends SCO, aligning SDC models with primary existing BFO-compliant sustainability ontologies. We intend ClimOO-SDC2 as an initial starting point to establish a unique BFO-compliant representation of climate and climate change. 

To construct ClimOO-SDC2, we proceed as follows (focus on OWL classes; we followed the same approach concerning the other OWL building blocks).
• If the class was not relevant, we did not import it.
• If the class was relevant and adequate, we directly imported it.
• If the class was relevant but inadequately axiomatized, we created a corresponding class that supports appropriate axioms but maintains the local identifier of the original SDC Onto class. We opted for this solution to offer a direct strategy of reference to the original version from which SDC2 has been forked. In the future, alternative, possibly more robust, strategies can be implemented. Exceptions: Given their centrality in the model, the following class has been supplied with ClimOO local identifiers and annotated towards original SDC Onto classes:
   • climate
   • climate change
   • (atmospheric) weather
   • climate system process
   • climate system component 
• If the class, despite axiomatization, was misleading, we did not import it, and we created adequate class(es) as needed. We supplied it with a ClimOO local identifier.
When revising classes, we complied with BFO and OBO-Foundry best practices.

All SDC2 building blocks support the following namespace to ensure appropriate identification and fairness: https://www.w3id.org/climoo/climoo-sdc2#"""@en ;
                                           owl:versionInfo "2026-05-15"@en ,
                                                           "V1.0.0."@en ;
                                           <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note> """Repository: https://www.w3id.org/climoo/repo
Documentation webpage: https://www.w3id.org/climoo/docs"""@en ,
                                                                                      "The most recent version of this file is available on GitHub at the following link: https://www.w3id.org/climoo/climoo-sdc2."@en .

